| The Dangers of a Patent War Chest                                  |
|   from the not-more-powerful-quicker-easier-the-dark-side-is dept. |
|   posted by Zonk on Saturday June 09, @13:29 (Patents)             |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/09/1647211          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]Timothy B. Lee writes "I've got an article in the New York Times in
which I make the case against software patents. Expanding on a point I
first made on my blog, I point out that [1]Microsoft has had a change of
heart on the patent issue. In 1991, Bill Gates worried that 'some large
company will patent some obvious thing' and use it to blackmail smaller
companies. Now that [2]Microsoft is a large company with a patent
war-chest of their own, they don't seem so concerned about abuse of the
patent system. I then describe how Verizon's efforts to shut down Vonage
are a perfect illustration of Gates' fears."

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/09/1647211

Links:
